        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30681",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'll update the documentation. In the mean time, here's what you need to know:\n* Any additional arguments in excess of 2 passed to setClass() are considered invocation arguments\n* Invocation arguments are appended to any arguments passed to the method call prior to calling the method\n\nAs an example, if you do the following:\n{code}\n$server->setClass('Foo', 'foo', 'hello', 'world');\n{code}\n\nThen you will have two invocation arguments, 'hello', and 'world'. If you then call the method 'foo.bar', which maps to the method 'bar' in class Foo, as follows: \n{code}\nfoo.bar('baz');\n{code}\nThen the actual call will be:\n{code}\nfoo.bar('baz', 'hello', 'world');\n{code}\nIn other words, the arguments you provided to setClass() are now passed as additional arguments to the method call.\n\nOne way this is useful is for passing an authentication token to each service method; your service class can then pull it off the end and check ACLs prior to executing any work.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-05T05:25:08.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-05T05:25:08.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33799",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lars",
                        "name": "lars",
                        "displayName": "Lars Strojny",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "So far the theory. Reality is, that this will never work because of:\n\n{code:title=Zend\/XmlRpc\/Server.php}\n    public function setClass($class, $namespace = '', $argv = null)\n    {\n        if (is_string($class) && !class_exists($class)) {\n            if (!class_exists($class)) {\n                #require_once 'Zend\/XmlRpc\/Server\/Exception.php';\n                throw new Zend_XmlRpc_Server_Exception('Invalid method class', 610);\n            }\n        }\n\n        $argv = null;\n        if (3 < func_num_args()) {\n            $argv = func_get_args();\n            $argv = array_slice($argv, 3);\n        }\n\n{code}\n\nIf $argv is set, func_num_args() will return 3, not > 3. And it will never reach the slice() call, which is wrong too (should be offset 2, not offset 3).",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lars",
                        "name": "lars",
                        "displayName": "Lars Strojny",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-08-22T18:05:56.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-08-22T18:07:57.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33800",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lars",
                        "name": "lars",
                        "displayName": "Lars Strojny",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The behavior is now fixed so that it works as documented.",
